Human-Readable Deed
This deed is non-normative. The legal code controls.
- Attribution: Requires normal attribution and license notice retention when the work is shared.
- Commercial Use: Blocks monetized or commercial use of the work.
- Modification: People may create and distribute modified versions, subject to the rest of the license.
- Redistribution: Redistribution is allowed, subject to the rest of the license.
- Derivative Obligations: Modified files must say what changed and when.
- Resale: No one may sell the work itself.
- AI & Training: Prevents the work from being used to train or evaluate machine-learning systems.
- Ethical Restrictions: Blocks surveillance, profiling, and non-consensual biometric monitoring.
- Ethical Restrictions: Blocks disinformation, synthetic manipulation, and deceptive influence campaigns.
- Branding: Mostly restricts trademark and brand use except for basic origin references.
- Branding Add-ons: Prevents downstream parties from white-labeling or disguising the origin.
- Hosting & SaaS: Prevents the work from being offered as a hosted service.
- Patents: Grants a limited patent license tied to the work and terminates on patent aggression.
- Patent Defense Add-ons: Suspends patent rights if the licensee launches offensive patent claims around the work.
- Education & Research: Prevents turning the work into a competing commercial course or curriculum.
- Education & Research: Blocks courses or curricula that compete with the licensor’s educational offering.
- Education & Research: Blocks certification, credential, exam, or assessment extraction.
- Compliance & Governance: Requires privacy-law compliance when the work processes personal data.
- Compliance & Governance: Requires a security review before high-risk deployment.

